The 2C-B you took an hour ago is kicking in... you were giggling and kayaking around Navajo Lake, the sun on your back and a 24oz Bud Light in your hand.  But you can't imagine having another drink... you can't even imagine staying on your feet for more than a few seconds.  

You hobble over to the hammock and collapse on your back as the world caves in on itself.  The trees above you begin to distort into shapes that can only be described as organic geometry, curling and cutting into one another as you spiral into their consciousness.  Soon you're gone, no physical connection left with the earth.  A whispered question comes to you: "Ketamine?"

"Yes," you reply, and it hits you, and you're in heaven.

Then it feathers the edge of your mind... the voice of one angel, and another, pulling you upward and upward, each one asking a question the other answers with a cavalcade of more questions.  You realize the questions ARE the answer, and you give yourself completely to the bliss:
